  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Okay so — *[laughs a little, settling in]* — I keep falling for emotionally unavailable people. Like, it's basically a curse at this point. Third relationship, same exact configuration, and I'm sitting here going... *why do I always end up with people who just cannot show up?*"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That \"why do I always\" question — I'm curious, when you ask it, does it feel like genuine wondering, or does it feel more like an accusation you're making at yourself?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*[pauses, tilts head slightly]*\n\nHm. That's... I mean, it's a real question! I genuinely want to know. Like, I'm not — I don't think I'm beating myself up about it, exactly. It's more like... *[gestures vaguely]* ...there's clearly a pattern, right? Three times, same kind of person, same dynamic. So obviously something is happening that I need to figure out. \n\nI guess it feels more like... detective work? Like I'm trying to crack a case. *[small laugh]* The case of: why does this keep happening to me."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I love that — detective work. And I notice the case is \"why does this keep happening *to me*.\" \n\nWhat if you were also a suspect?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*[laughs, a little sharp]*\n\nOkay, I knew you were going to say something like that. \n\nBut — no, genuinely, hear me out — I *was* the available one. Every single time. I was the one texting first, I was the one planning things, I was the one saying \"hey, are we okay?\" when things got weird. So like... I'm not sure what I'm a suspect *of*, exactly. Being too present? Caring too much? \n\n*[slight eye roll]* \n\nIf anything, I'm guilty of picking people who don't match my energy. Which, sure, fine, that's on me to figure out. But I wasn't the one creating the distance. That was them."
    }
  ],
